'''FBC White Star''' are a [[Peru]]vian [[association football|football]] club based in [[Arequipa]], [[Arequipa Region]]. The women's football department of the club won the national league in 2009, and competed in that season's [[2009 Copa Libertadores de F<U+00FA>tbol Femenino|Copa Libertadores]].

==History==
The club is recognized in [[Arequipa]] as one of the five "big" teams together with [[FBC Pierola]], [[Sportivo Hurac<U+00E1>n]], [[FBC Melgar]] and [[FBC Aurora]], despite they being the only one of these that has failed to participate in the First Division.

The women's football department of the club won the Campeonato Nacional de F<U+00FA>tbol Femenino in 2009, after beating Estudiantes  Universitarios de Cusco 3-2 in the final,<ref name="nationalleague">{{cite web|title=White, campe<U+00F3>n|url=http://www.correoperu.com.pe/correo/nota.php?txtEdi_id=5&txtSecci_parent=0&txtSecci_id=18&txtNota_id=29302|accessdate=August 13, 2009|publisher=Correo Peru|language=Spanish}}</ref> and thus qualifying to compete in [[2009 Copa Libertadores de F<U+00FA>tbol Femenino|that year]]'s [[Copa Libertadores de F<U+00FA>tbol Femenino|Copa Libertadores]].<ref name="copalibertadores">{{cite web|title=White Star en la Copa|url=http://www.correoperu.com.pe/correo/nota.php?txtEdi_id=5&txtSecci_id=18&txtSecci_parent=0&txtNota_id=91880|accessdate=August 13, 2009|publisher=Correo Peru|language=Spanish}}</ref>

==Rivalries==
FBC White Star has had a long standing rivalry with [[FBC Melgar]], [[FBC Aurora]], [[FBC Pierola]], and [[Sportivo Hurac<U+00E1>n]].

